        {# P01 MASTHEAD #}
        <div class="reveal pattern">
          <div class="pattern__label"><span class="eyebrow">P · 01 · Masthead</span></div>
          <div class="pattern__frame">
            <div class="eyebrow">Council</div>
            <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 300; font-size: clamp(38px, 5vw, 64px); line-height: 1.04; letter-spacing: -0.016em; margin: var(--gap-5) 0; max-width: 22ch;">Ontario Indigenous AI &amp; Technology Council</h1>
            <p style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-style: italic; font-weight: 300; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--ink-2); max-width: 44ch;">A council of two, working to improve the digital systems that deliver services to First Nations.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        {# P02 PREMISE #}
        <div class="reveal pattern">
          <div class="pattern__label"><span class="eyebrow">P · 02 · Premise</span></div>
          <div class="pattern__frame">
            <div class="eyebrow">Premise</div>
            <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 300; font-size: clamp(28px, 3.4vw, 44px); line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin: var(--gap-5) 0;">The systems meant to serve First Nations are rarely chosen by them.</h2>
            <p class="body body--wide">First Nations are routinely handed digital systems &mdash; case-management tools, data platforms, AI &mdash; chosen by vendors or administrators without the communities those systems are meant to serve. The result is software that doesn't fit, data that flows to the wrong places, and services that suffer for it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

